### Problem18


The time complexity of the binary search algorithm is O(_____(0)\___)(1/n/logn/nlogn/n^2). The best-case time complexity would be O(_____(1)\___)(1/n/logn/nlogn/n^2) when the central index would directly match the desired value. The worst-case scenario could be the values at either extremity of the list or values not in the list.
